					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602#post-4864496</guid>
				<title>Perplexing scenario about the past, and the future of SCP Series</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602/scp-series-6#post-4864496</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jan 2021 18:20:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Achemarfit</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2612361</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm a nobody, and haven't written in years (luckily for you because my writing for the past few years has been shit). However I've still followed, lightly, what's been going on with this community since 2015. I still find it strange, almost concerning that we're nearing Series VII, the SCP-6XXX series. It doesn't feel right, even Series III didn't feel right. Somehow, somewhere, deep down I feel as if post Series II (hell, maybe even Series I) doesn't feel right, natural, or believable. From simple stories about a vague entity studying creative takes on classic monsters and ideas, to esoteric gods and dimensions, back to an almost self-deprecating metaverse of irony.</p> <p>I don't feel the sense of coherence, the idea that everything's under control, until when it's not. It seems as if everyone is vying for their chance to write the <em>Next Big SCP Apocalypse Article!</em> I want articles that expand our knowledge of the anomalous, the test logs, the interview logs, the recovery logs, what even is the Foundation as a part of our universe than just the aching backbone of a 70 year old man?</p> <p>The culture of video games, movie shorts, RP servers, and pop Youtube has had its heavy mark on this community, down to the core. This is all my mere opinion, however. I haven't engaged heavily (and more often then not at all) here for years, and if someone could help me with this question. <em>What the hell is going on, in the world these entities reside in?</em></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
