					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602#post-4558676</guid>
				<title>Re: Jumping the shark?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602/scp-series-6#post-4558676</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2020 22:51:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>barredowl</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6001754</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Eh, I would disagree with you there. If anything, the site has arguably gotten <em>more</em> popular, and ideas have only become more diverse and interesting. In my opinion, a lot of Series I articles feel very uniform and basic and feel more like a page ripped out of a DnD manual. I think more than ever authors are starting to explore the possibilities the medium of an SCP article can provide. Instead of every article being a baseline description of a cool thing, authors are experimenting with writing articles including storylines and emotions which in earlier times were few and far between. And there's a lot of interesting stuff which has come out of newer articles (check <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/user-curated-lists">these</a> lists if you want some recommendations).</p> <p>As for the SCP universe &quot;having its corpse paraded around&quot;? Well, it's a collaborative writing project, and I think it would be a tough task to convince the wiki to stop writing new things. A lot of people (including me) find solace in the writing community here, and would probably refuse any attempt to blockade their creativity. Whether or not anyone likes it, the wiki is here to stay.</p> <p>Well, that rant got a little unhinged at the end, but my point is, there's a lot of cool stuff springing forth on the wiki &#8212; you just have to discover where it is.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602#post-4558660</guid>
				<title>Jumping the shark?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13021602/scp-series-6#post-4558660</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2020 22:23:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Researcher Miserie</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6135382</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>How many more series can the SCP Foundation realistically produce? Call me pessimistic, but it seems like the site is starting to become oversaturated with articles. It seems as though people began running out of ideas around Series III or Series IV, and I'm worried we're in the process of jumping the shark.<br /> I guess I'd rather have the SCP universe go out with a bang than have its corpse paraded around like its probable inspiration, Doctor Who.</p> <p>Just my opinion though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
